               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origDate calendar="gregorian" when="1785">No internal date. Dated to circa 1785 by Vinson in Vinson et al. (1866-) and to 1785 by Cabaton (1912), on unstated grounds (presumably palaeographical and material analysis arguments). Not after 1854, since part of the collection of <persName role="collector">Édouard Ariel</persName> (1818-1854), bequested in 1855 to the Société Asiatique, Paris (Rosny 1868).</origDate>
                     
                  <origPlace>Tamilnadu.</origPlace></origin>
                  <acquisition>
                     <p>Received, August 1st, 1866, from the Société Asiatique. See BnF, département des Manuscrits, inventaire 7 = <title>Dons: manuscrits et imprimés documentaires, 1848-1895</title>, no. 1192.</p>
                  </acquisition>
               <provenance><p>Owned by <persName role="collector">Édouard Ariel</persName> (1818-1854). Bequested by Édouard Ariel to Société Asiatique (Rosny 1868, p. 177).</p></provenance></history>
